com.github.xemiru.general.stock

Class DefaultHelpGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.xemiru.general.stock.DefaultHelpGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HelpGenerator

    public class DefaultHelpGenerator
extends Object
implements HelpGenerator
    The default implementation of a HelpGenerator.

    Pagination is disabled.

    Command sorting is alphabetical.

    The list of commands with their short help text is output in the following format:

    (command name)\t(command short description)

    Full help text for commands is output in the following format:

     Command: (command name)
 Aliases: (aliases OR "(no aliases)")
 Syntax: (syntax)

 (description OR "This command has no description.")

    The error message for unknown commands is:

    "Couldn't find command (input). Try 'help'."

    The error message for commands that crash during information harvesting is:

    "That command crashed when we tried to ask it about itself. Oops."

      • getPageSize

        public int getPageSize(CommandContext context)
        Description copied from interface: HelpGenerator
        Returns the amount of items to be shown in a page.

        Use 0 or a negative number to disable pagination for calls to HelpGenerator.sendHelp(CommandContext, TreeMap, int, int). The method will always receive 0 as the requested and max page if this is disabled.

        The value can be adapted based on the provided context.

        Specified by:
        getPageSize in interface HelpGenerator
        Parameters:
        context - the context executing the help command
        Returns:
        the amount of items to be shown in a help page

      • sendHelp

        public void sendHelp(CommandContext context,
                     TreeMap<String,Optional<String>> help,
                     int page,
                     int maxPage)
        Description copied from interface: HelpGenerator
        Sends help text.

        Items within the passed map are already the product of pagination; one does not need the page parameter to perform it themselves. The page and maxPage parameters exists purely to be able to relay such information back to the user.

        It is possible to receive an empty map if the user attempts to provide a page out of bounds.

        Specified by:
        sendHelp in interface HelpGenerator
        Parameters:
        context - the context executing the help command
        help - the mapping of command names to short descriptions
        page - the requested page
        maxPage - the max page
